# DormDrop ŌĆö Style Rules

## Purpose

This document defines the aesthetic and implementation constraints for DormDrop's frontend. Every component, page, and interaction must follow these rules. The goal is a UI that feels intentionally designed ŌĆö not like default Tailwind, not like a template, not like AI slop.

---

## Non-Negotiables

- **No border-radius on structural elements.** Modals, panels, inputs, buttons, cards, dropdowns ŌĆö all sharp corners. Rounded corners are permitted only on: avatar containers, status pills/badges, toggle thumbs, and spinner elements.
- **No blue anywhere.** Not for buttons, links, focus rings, alerts, or any interactive element. Pick a brand accent and commit to it. Blue is the default of defaults ŌĆö it signals "nobody made a decision here."
- **No native browser controls.** No `alert()`, `confirm()`, `prompt()`, no native `<select>`, no native checkboxes. Every interactive element is custom.
- **No bold button text.** Button labels are normal weight. Emphasis comes from background contrast and spatial hierarchy, not font weight.
- **No cold grays.** Use warm neutrals (stone, sand, warm gray). Cold `gray-*` tones are banned from the palette.

---

## Typography

- Pick a distinctive display/brand font. Do not use Inter, Roboto, Arial, or system-ui for display text. Body text can use a clean sans-serif but it should not be the same font every AI project defaults to.
- Weight hierarchy: 400 is the baseline. 500 for labels and emphasis. 600 for modal titles and section headers only. Never go above 600 in the UI.
- Size hierarchy: `text-xs` for metadata/labels, `text-sm` for body/inputs, `text-base`+ reserved for headings. The UI should feel compact and dense, not spacious and bloated.
- Primary text and secondary/muted text must have clearly distinct colors ŌĆö not just opacity differences.

---

## Color System

- Define a single brand accent color. Use it sparingly: focus rings, active states, key highlights. Overuse kills it.
- Define exactly one dark color for primary CTA button backgrounds.
- Surface colors should be warm, not white. Use off-whites and warm neutrals for backgrounds, panels, and table headers.
- Selection highlight (`::selection`) should use a tinted version of the brand accent.
- Keep the overall palette tight ŌĆö 6-8 intentional colors max. If you're reaching for a new color, you probably need to reuse an existing one.

---

## Borders & Dividers

- Default borders: subtle, low-contrast. They separate content without competing with it.
- Define two border weights: a default for inputs/cards, and a subtler one for section separators.
- Focus states must be visible but not jarring. Use the brand accent or primary dark color ŌĆö never browser-default blue outline.
- Focus pattern: `focus:outline-none` + custom border/ring treatment. Always.

---

## Buttons

Four tiers, no more:

1. **Primary** ŌĆö dark background, white text. The only "loud" button on any screen.
2. **Secondary/Ghost** ŌĆö no background, muted text, darkens on hover.
3. **Outlined** ŌĆö border, no fill, subtle hover background.
4. **Destructive** ŌĆö red background, white text. Used only for irreversible actions.

Rules:
- Every button gets `transition-colors` on hover.
- Every async button gets `disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed`.
- Loading state: inline spinner inside the button, not a separate loader.
- One primary button per view/modal. If there are two, you haven't decided what the real action is.

---

## Inputs

- Consistent height across the app. Pick `h-10` or `h-12` and commit.
- Placeholder text is always muted/secondary color.
- Focus border uses brand accent or primary dark ŌĆö never default browser outline.
- No border-radius.
- Floating labels or standard label-above patterns are both fine, but pick one and use it everywhere.

---

## Modals

- Render via `createPortal` to `document.body`. No z-index gambling.
- Overlay: semi-transparent black. Click-to-close on overlay for non-destructive actions.
- Structure: header (title left, close icon right, bottom border) ŌåÆ scrollable body ŌåÆ footer (cancel left, primary action right, top border).
- `max-h-[90vh]` to prevent viewport overflow. Body scrolls, header/footer are fixed.
- No border-radius on modal panel.
- Destructive modals: no overlay click-to-close, destructive button style on primary action.

---

## Dropdowns & Menus

- Custom dropdown components only. No native `<select>`.
- Enter animation: subtle scale + opacity transition (0.1-0.2s).
- Items: consistent padding, hover background, pointer cursor.
- No border-radius on dropdown panel.

---

## Cards & Listings

- Cards are the core unit of the marketplace. They must feel tactile but not heavy.
- Image-forward: the photo is the primary element, text is secondary.
- Price is always visually prominent ŌĆö it's the first thing a buyer scans for after the image.
- Status indicators (sold, reserved, expired) use small pills/badges ŌĆö these are the exception where rounded corners are allowed.
- Hover state on cards: subtle lift (shadow change) or border highlight. Not both.

---

## Icons

- Pick one icon library and use it consistently. Do not mix icon sets.
- Inline with text: 14-16px. Standalone action icons: 18-20px.
- Icon color: inherit from text color or use secondary/muted. Hover to primary.

---

## Spacing & Density

- The UI should feel compact. This is a utility app, not a marketing site.
- Prefer `gap-2`/`gap-3` over `gap-4`/`gap-6` for most layouts.
- Padding inside cards/panels: `p-3` or `p-4`, not `p-6` or `p-8`.
- Whitespace is a tool ŌĆö use it to create hierarchy, not to fill space.

---

## Animations & Transitions

- `transition-colors duration-200` is the default for any hover/focus state.
- Page/section transitions: subtle slide or fade. Nothing bouncy, nothing slow.
- Loading spinners: small, inline, using border-based CSS animation.
- Skeleton loaders for content that takes >200ms to load. Gray shimmer on warm neutral, not pulsing opacity.

---

## Responsive

- Mobile-first. This app will be used on phones in dorm hallways more than on desktops.
- Listing grid: 1 column on mobile, 2 on tablet, 3-4 on desktop.
- Bottom sheet pattern for modals on mobile instead of centered overlay.
- Touch targets: minimum 44px height on interactive elements for mobile.

---

## What Not To Do

- No `rounded-lg` or `rounded-xl` on structural elements.
- No blue in any form.
- No generic font stacks (Inter, Roboto, system-ui for display).
- No native browser UI elements.
- No bold button text.
- No cold gray palette.
- No gratuitous gradients or glassmorphism.
- No drop shadows heavier than `shadow-md` on cards.
- No hover animations that take longer than 200ms.
- No layout shifts on interaction ŌĆö if something expands/collapses, it should be animated and predictable.
- No inconsistent spacing ŌĆö if two similar components have different padding, that's a bug.
